raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "django-log-request-id" %}
{% set version = "2.1.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/django-log-request-id-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: b11fc821774b54b820ef2e732dbaa52304711de8d5c4f9031ca48578f6121ab6

build:
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  number: 1

requirements:
  host:
    - python {{ python_min }}
    - pip
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python >={{ python_min }}
    - django >=1.8

test:
  imports:
    - log_request_id
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip
    - python {{ python_min }}

about:
  home: https://github.com/dabapps/django-log-request-id/
  summary: Django middleware and log filter to attach a unique ID to every log message generated as part of a request
  license: BSD-2-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - rxm7706
